description:
### DeDup

The challenge involves the creation of a function `deDup` which takes an array of integers as input and removes all duplicate elements. The output should be an array with the same elements but without any duplicates.

Input: An array of integers `{INPUT_DESCRIPTION}`
Output: An array of integers without any duplicates `{OUTPUT_DESCRIPTION}`

Example:

```java
deDup([1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3]); // [1, 2, 3] 
```
